

**PF3 \- Treasury Newsletter – Comprehensive Process Flow (with Beehiiv Integration)**

1. **Trigger & Frequency**  
* **Trigger:** Scheduled (daily or weekly; set via Make)  
* **Override:** Manual start via browser bookmark or Beehiiv’s dashboard

---

2. **Article Aggregation**  
* **Sources:** Up to 30 articles pulled from RSS (Inoreader or Google News Boards) focused on treasury, finance, AI, and technology.  
* **Filters:** Applied based on tags, topics, publisher, popularity…  
* **Deduplication:** Ensures only unique, new articles (tracked by Google Sheet).

---

3. **AI-Driven Curation and Commentary**  
* **Step:** Make sends article batch (title, summary, URL) to ChatGPT with a prompting supplement document that provides additional details on target market, tone, objectives, etc. stored on the google drive.  
* **Prompt:** "Select the top 10 articles for treasury/finance leaders based on the parameters provided in the prompting supplement document. For each, return: title, URL, and 50-75-word combined summary and expert commentary on why this matters."  
* **Output:** Returns top 10 articles with summaries/commentary.

---

4. **AI-Driven Introduction and Wrap-up**  
* **Step:** Make sends the 10 article summary/commentary blurbs back to ChatGPT along with the supplemental prompting document to prompt ChatGPT to draft an introduction and wrap-up to the newsletter based on the content that will be included.   
* **Prompt:** "Based on the 10 articles selected and the summary/commentary blurbs created, draft an introduction and a wrap-up to the newletter."  
* **Output:** Returns introduction and wrap-up for the newsletter.

---

5. **Visuals & Metadata**  
* **Step:** For each chosen article, use OpenGraph or scraping API to pull the main thumbnail/image.  
* **If missing:** Insert branded default or category image.  
* **All metadata (title, URL, publisher, summary, image URL, AI commentary)** logged in Google Sheet for this issue.

---

6. **Newsletter Assembly in Beehiiv**  
* **Step:** Use Make to create a new Beehiiv draft issue.  
* **Macro Introduction and Wrap-up** to lead the newsletter and complete the newsletter with the 10 article thumbnails and summary/commentary blurbs in between.  
* **Content:** For each article, create a section with:  
  * Article image/thumbnail (URL)  
  * Title (hyperlinked)  
  * Publisher/Date  
  * AI summary / AI commentary ("Why it matters")  
  * “Read more” link  
* **Editorial Note:** Optionally add a personal intro or macro-commentary at the top.

---

7. **Preview & Editing**  
* **Action:** Notify you (or editor) that draft is ready in Beehiiv.  
* **QC:** Final edits, reordering, or image tweaks can be made directly in Beehiiv’s drag-and-drop editor.

---

8. **Distribution via Beehiiv**  
* **Step:** When approved, issue is published in Beehiiv.  
* **Email Function:** Beehiiv automatically sends the newsletter to all subscribers with built-in deliverability and anti-spam protections.  
* **Web Version:** Issue is posted to your Beehiiv-hosted newsletter site for browsing/sharing.  
* **Optional:** Auto-post to LinkedIn, X, or Teams using Beehiiv’s integrations or Zapier.

---

9. **Logging & Archiving**  
* **Google Sheet:** Record sent issue (date, articles, commentary, unique ID, Beehiiv URL).  
* **Cloud Storage:** PDF or HTML archive of each newsletter saved to Google Drive, SharePoint, or OneDrive.

---

10. **Analytics & Engagement**  
* **Beehiiv Analytics:** Automatic tracking of:  
  * Open rates  
  * Click-throughs per article/link  
  * Subscriber growth/churn  
  * Top-performing content  
* **Data Export:** Make will sync analytics back to the master Google Sheet for dashboards and executive reporting.

---

11. **Feedback & Iteration**  
* **User Survey:** Include a Beehiiv poll or “Reply with Feedback” button.  
* **Manual Additions:** Subscribers or team can submit articles for next issue via Google Form or Beehiiv’s submission tools.

---

12. **Key Data Fields for Google Sheet Tracking**  
* Issue Date/ID  
* Article Title  
* Publisher  
* URL  
* Image URL  
* AI Summary  
* AI Commentary  
* Date Sent  
* Beehiiv Issue URL  
* Open Rate, CTR (from Beehiiv)  
* Editor/Reviewer  
* Link to Google Drive archive
